fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "Modules.html#page-description", "fragment": "<div id=\"page-description\" data-hotdoc-source=\"Modules.md\">\n<h1 id=\"modules\">Modules</h1>\n<p>In addition to core language features, Meson also provides a module system aimed at providing helper methods for common build operations. Using modules is simple, first you import them:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-meson\">mymod = import('somemodule')\n</code></pre>\n<p>After this you can use the returned object to use the functionality provided:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-meson\">mymod.do_something('text argument')\n</code></pre>\n<p>Meson has a selection of modules to make common requirements easy to\nuse. Modules can be thought of like the standard library of a\nprogramming language. Currently Meson provides the modules listed on\nsubpages.</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n        "});